		    <title class="- topic/title ">
			      <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">16.303</ph> Cost-sharing contracts.</title>
		    <conbody class="- topic/body concept/conbody ">
			      <ol id="d989e13" class="- topic/ol ">
				        <li class="- topic/li ">
					          <p id="d1003e17" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(a)</ph>
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
						            
						            <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">Description.</i> A cost-sharing contract is a cost-reimbursement contract in which the contractor receives no fee and is reimbursed only for an agreed-upon portion of its allowable costs.</p>
				        </li>
				        <li class="- topic/li ">
					          <p id="d1003e29" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(b)</ph>
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
						            
						            <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">Application</i>. A cost-sharing contract may be used when the contractor agrees to absorb a portion of the costs, in the expectation of substantial compensating benefits.</p>
				        </li>
				        <li class="- topic/li ">
					          <p id="d1003e41" class="- topic/p ">
